The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, July 12, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																The Event				 																																	(Seagull  Arts and Media Resource Centre, July 14 to 18) The film fare  this week includes Hamlet, Ran, Julius Caesar,  King Lear and Othello. Watch out for more next  week. The festival, organised in association with Deshbandhu  College for Girls, is on till August 2.  The Seminar				 																																	(Bangla  Akademi, July 14, 3 pm) To celebrate Global Day of Action  Against Waste Incarceration, Disha, in association the West  Bengal Municipal Association, has organised a discussion on  eco-friendly waste management system, with eminent speakers  from various fields.  The Book				 																																	(Editor:  Asghar Ali Engineer) This book is a compilation of articles,  editorials, investigative reports, surveys, memoranda and  other material on the carnage. It is an attempt to preserve  the lessons learnt in one of the most horrifying events in  modern Indian history.  THE album				 																																	(Music:  Tabun Sutradhar) Jagjit Singh, Asha Bhosle, Adnan Sami and  our very own Usha Uthup make up the singing cast of this Subhas  Ghai film. The fusion soundtrack experiments with accompaniments  of traditional genres like ghazals. It is also a first on  the anti-piracy CD shelves. 

